*===========================================================
* Overview:
* - This is a raw, buggy, unsupported conversion of the C3 wasp agent.
* - Behaviours include roaming, hunting food, retaliating when pushed, and dying/rotting.
* - Some variables and routines are unused or redundant.

* Object Variables (ovXX):
* - ov00 = State (0 = roam, 1 = seek food, 99 = die)
* - ov01 = Age counter (used in death routine)
* - ov02 = Hunger/energy level (decreases over time, increased when eating)
* - ov10/ov11 = Movement direction (X/Y)
* - ov16 = Current target (food/enemy)
* - ov17 = Attacker/pusher reference
* - ov61 = Bioenergy (life force, corpse state)
* - ov72 = Food energy gain (+400 when eating)
* - ov73 = Hunger threshold (400)
* - ov74 = Fullness threshold (800)
* - ov88 = Attack timer (counts down from 80)
* - UNUSED: ov05 (life stage), ov06 (gender), ov20 (sex drive), ov75 (food flag), ov89 (aggression flag)

* Subroutines:
* - Active: die_, gfod (get food), atak (attack), roam, obst (obstacle check),
*           vect (vector choice), anim (animation), move, find (search), hunt (chase target)
* - Unused: swrm (swarming behavior, never called), near (commented out in attack)

* Known Redundancies / Issues:
* - Duplicate death check in timer script.
* - ov05, ov06, ov20, ov75, ov89 are initialized but never used.
* - swrm and near subroutines are defined/commented but not integrated.
* - Corpse script checks carr = null twice (redundant).
* - Attack routine has commented-out feeding logic.
* - Obstacle routine has commented-out floor detection.

